==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*beran-'', from Indo-European ''*bher-'' ‘brown’.  Cognate with Old High German [[bero]] (German [[Bär]]), Middle Dutch [[bere]] (Dutch [[beer]]), Old Norse ''ber-'' ‘bears’ (used in compounds).  A North Germanic variant, ''*bernu-'', gave Old Norse [[bjǫrn]] ‘bear’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bera/

===Noun===
'''bera''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''beran''')
# a [[bear]]

